### 7. BACKEND vs. FRONTEND CONTROL ANALYSIS

| Feature | Currently | Controlled By | Adding Feature Requires |
|---------|-----------|---|---|
| Product names (shopping, cashback, etc.) | Backend ✓ | API response | Card layout + icon logic |
| Product icons | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend mapping | Code + NAME_TO_ICON update |
| Filter period options | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend | Code change |
| Transaction type labels (Ganhos, Usados) | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend TYPE_LABELS | Code change |
| Help text in modals | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend strings | Code + design system |
| SLA time ("Até 72h") | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend | Code change |
| Support phone numbers | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend | Code change |
| Button text labels | **Hardcoded** ✗ | Frontend | Code change |
| Transaction categorization logic | **String matching** ✗ | Frontend rules | Fragile + breaks easily |
| FAQ content | Backend ✓ | API response | Store state + fetch |
| Marketplace link | Backend ✓ | API redirectURL | WebView delegation |

---

### 8. PROBLEMATIC PATTERNS

#### **Pattern 1: Brittle String Matching for Categorization**

**PointsDetail/utils.ts - Lines 40-48:**
```typescript
const tagIndicators = [
  'tag', 'pedágio', 'pedagio', 'estacionamento', 
  'abastecimento', 'abastece', 'drive', 'lava', 'rápido',
];

const isTag = tagIndicators.some(
  indicator =>
    icon.includes(indicator) ||
    description.includes(indicator) ||
    provider.includes(indicator),
);
```

**Risks**:
- Case sensitivity issues (handled by toLowerCase, but regex would be safer)
- Diacritical variations not fully handled
- No escaping for special characters
- If backend changes "abastecimento" → "abast", feature breaks

#### **Pattern 2: Dual Naming Conventions**

**useCardBuilderWhereUseMyPoints/index.ts - Lines 85-106:**
```typescript
const rawCF =
  (product as any).conversionFactor ??
  (product as any).convertionFactor ??
  0;

const productCode =
  (product as any).productCode ?? (product as any).code;

const campaingId =
  (product as any).campaingId ??
  (product as any).campaignId ??
  undefined;
```

**Problem**: Backend sends inconsistent field names (typo: "campaingId" vs correct "campaignId"), forcing frontend to handle both.

#### **Pattern 3: Empty Default Values in DTO Mapping**

**extract.repository.ts - Lines 183-198:**
```typescript
function getTransactionFromDto(dto: TransactionDto): PointsTransaction {
  return {
    // ...
    details: {
      provider: '',      // Should come from backend!
      extraInfo: '',
      fields: [],
    },
    // ...
  };
}
```

Then PointsDetail/utils.ts expects these to be populated for categorization to work properly.

---

### 9. DYNAMIC CONTENT CLAIMING TO BE DYNAMIC BUT ISN'T

#### **"Dynamic" Marketplace (Not Really)**

**RewardProgramMarketplace/view.tsx - Lines 1-70:**
```typescript
const RewardProgramMarketplaceWebViewView = ({
  uri,
  webViewRef,
  // ...
}: RewardProgramMarketplaceWebViewProps) => {
  return (
    <BasicScreen title="Shopping" ...>
      <Box>
        <WebView
          ref={webViewRef}
          source={{ uri }}
          style={{ width, height }}
          // ... props
        />
      </Box>
    </BasicScreen>
  );
};
```

**Data Flow**: 
1. Frontend requests `/marketplace` endpoint
2. Backend returns `{ dados: { redirectURL: "https://example.com/marketplace" } }`
3. Frontend just wraps it in WebView

**Reality**: Not truly dynamic to frontend - it's a delegate. Everything inside WebView is out of frontend's control. Changing product offerings requires no mobile app update (good!), but also means frontend has zero say in UX.

#### **"Dynamic" FAQ (Actually Backend-Driven)**

**LearnMoreRewardProgram/index.tsx - Lines 68-105:**
```typescript
const items = useMemo((): propsItems[] => {
  if (
    typeof selectedCategory?.value === 'string' ||
    !selectedCategory?.value?.questions ||
    !selectedCategory?.category
  ) {
    return [];
  }

  return selectedCategory.value.questions.map((
    item: { question: string; answer: string },
    index: number,
  ): propsItems => {
    return {
      id: index,
      title: item.question,
      text: item.answer,
      // ... styling
    } as propsItems;
  });
}, [selectedCategory]);
```

**True Dynamic**: FAQ content comes from backend, but:
- Q&A structure is rigid (only question + answer)
- Cannot add images, links, or rich formatting to answers
- No markdown or HTML support
- Cannot reorder questions dynamically

